{
    "tha-ap490:0.1_0": "The senior monks, Householders,",
    "tha-ap490:0.2_0": "Putting rags",
    "tha-ap490:0.3_0": "he has laid down the burden.",
    "tha-ap490:1.1_0": "“He was this, Sir.",
    "tha-ap490:1.2_0": "from the world to the next,",
    "tha-ap490:1.3_0": "They crossed over the far shore,",
    "tha-ap490:1.4_0": "the Buddha came",
    "tha-ap490:10.1_0": "Just as a fine field,",
    "tha-ap490:10.2_0": "or even a seed,",
    "tha-ap490:10.3_0": "Reviewing their rightly,",
    "tha-ap490:10.4_0": "and now you’ll live on the fruit.’",
    "tha-ap490:11.1_0": "Just now you’re the Buddha,",
    "tha-ap490:11.2_0": "the one from whom you learn the Dhamma",
    "tha-ap490:11.3_0": "Reviewing their rightly,",
    "tha-ap490:11.4_0": "in which the fruit will grow.",
    "tha-ap490:12.1_0": "Setriving, resolute,",
    "tha-ap490:12.2_0": "peaceful and free of attachments;",
    "tha-ap490:12.3_0": "complete understanding",
    "tha-ap490:12.4_0": "and live without defilements.",
    "tha-ap490:13.1_0": "But for the eon",
    "tha-ap490:13.2_0": "from where deeds I want.",
    "tha-ap490:13.3_0": "I’m not aware of any bad places",
    "tha-ap490:13.4_0": "This is the fruit and result.",
    "tha-ap490:14.1_0": "My defilements have been burnt away by practicing absorption—",
    "tha-ap490:14.2_0": "... “I attained the noble ones,” ...",
    "tha-ap490:14.3_0": "and live without defilements.",
    "tha-ap490:15.1_0": "It was truly for me",
    "tha-ap490:15.2_0": "... “I attained the noble ones,” ...",
    "tha-ap490:15.3_0": "and fulfilled the Buddha’s instructions.”",
    "tha-ap490:16.1_0": "Attaining the four kinds of textual analysis",
    "tha-ap490:16.2_0": "... “I attained the noble ones,” ...",
    "tha-ap490:16.3_0": "and fulfilled the Buddha’s instructions.”",
    "tha-ap490:17.1_0": "That is how these verses were recited by the senior venerable Bakkula.",
    "tha-ap490:18.1_0": "and the eighth equipped.",
    "tha-ap490:2.1_0": "with water,",
    "tha-ap490:2.2_0": "they reach a safe place or a forest.",
    "tha-ap490:2.3_0": "I want to listen to the Buddha,",
    "tha-ap490:2.4_0": "and followed the world.",
    "tha-ap490:3.1_0": "“Let me leave the Buddha,",
    "tha-ap490:3.2_0": "the great sage invisible.",
    "tha-ap490:3.3_0": "I’ll do you,",
    "tha-ap490:3.4_0": "That is make an end of suffering.’",
    "tha-ap490:4.1_0": "Knowing my thoughts,",
    "tha-ap490:4.2_0": "the viper of the superb,",
    "tha-ap490:4.3_0": "I moving up my back,",
    "tha-ap490:4.4_0": "and stood to the world.",
    "tha-ap490:5.1_0": "since I gained myself",
    "tha-ap490:5.2_0": "since I attained understands.",
    "tha-ap490:5.3_0": "I have no happiness—",
    "tha-ap490:5.4_0": "as they are touched by the feet.",
    "tha-ap490:6.1_0": "Having understood the Awakened One,",
    "tha-ap490:6.2_0": "the viper of the superb,",
    "tha-ap490:6.3_0": "She wouldn’t leave",
    "tha-ap490:6.4_0": "these verses.",
    "tha-ap490:7.1_0": "‘Fourpassing the mind!",
    "tha-ap490:7.2_0": "and I remembered the Ganges.",
    "tha-ap490:7.3_0": "This king won’t stick",
    "tha-ap490:7.4_0": "wise, wouldn’t be wise.",
    "tha-ap490:8.1_0": "This with the ending of the Buddha,",
    "tha-ap490:8.2_0": "with a mind of love,",
    "tha-ap490:8.3_0": "But for the eon",
    "tha-ap490:8.4_0": "heavenly delight.",
    "tha-ap490:9.1_0": "and now I entered the host of gods,",
    "tha-ap490:9.2_0": "with bright words,",
    "tha-ap490:9.3_0": "Sitting alone, sitting alone,",
    "tha-ap490:9.4_0": "will surely doubt,"
}